						<summary>

						<p>Pāṇḍya, Jaṭāvarman Sundarapāṇḍya, 7th year = A.D. 1258.</p>						

						<p>This records that the trustees of the temple of Tiruvēṅgaivāyil sold some <hi rend="italic">dēvadāna</hi> land to a Mayilāppūr-uḍaiyāṉ Īsānadēvan to enjoy it under the <hi rend="italic">kuḍinīṅgā-dēvadāna</hi> tenure.</p>						

						<p>[Published in <hi rend="italic">IPS</hi>, No. 480.]</p>						

